        "text": "*[Bug 19019] interaction() should warn when coalescing levels*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19019>\n\n--- Comment #8 from Elin Waring (<mailto:elin.waring@gmail.com|elin.waring@gmail.com>) ---\nThis change causes this test to fail.\n<https:\/\/github.com\/r-devel\/r-svn\/blob\/f823e4ee67082620f53e5d1a5eadbca8542b094b\/tests\/reg-tests-1b.R#L719>\n\n```\n### Non-unique levels in factor should be forbidden from R 2.10.0 on\nc1 &lt;- c(\"a.b\",\"a\"); c2 &lt;- c(\"c\",\"b.c\")\nfi &lt;- interaction(c1, c2)\nstopifnot(length(lf &lt;- levels(fi)) == 3, lf[1] == \"a.b.c\",\n          identical(as.integer(fi), <http:\/\/rep.int|rep.int>(1L, 2)))\n## interaction() failed to produce unique levels before 2.9.1\n\n\n```\n\nBecause this would now produce a warning.  If there is another way to make\nnon-unique labels that does not involve the sep value and that does not require\nthat any of the factors have levels that are not unique we can change the test\ncase to that. \nOtherwise I would assert that the current case to expect a warning.\n\n\nI do think that most cases of this would be avoided if a less standard\nseparator were used (such as _._) as the default.",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
