        "text": "*[Bug 19019] interaction() should warn when coalescing levels*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19019>\n\n--- Comment #9 from Robert Schlicht (<mailto:robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de|robert.schlicht@tu-dresden.de>) ---\nMy guess is that the merging of levels was orginally introduced as a simple\nsolution for dealing with spurious duplicates with no effect on the analysis,\nperhaps in `reshape`.\n\nJust for `ave`, another solution would be assigning labels that do not contain\nseparators. I include an experimental version that also avoids the questionable\nmatching of doubles by their character representation in `as.factor`, although\nI am not yet convinced that (and the handling of NaNs) is a good idea as it\ncould break other things.\n```\nave_experimental &lt;- function (x, ..., FUN = mean)\n{\n  if(missing(...))\n    x[] &lt;- FUN(x)\n  else {\n    ifactor &lt;- function(y) {\n      if (is.factor(y))\n        lev &lt;- levels(y)\n      else {\n        lev &lt;- unique.default(y)\n        lev &lt;- lev[!<http:\/\/is.na|is.na>(lev)]\n        y &lt;- match(y, lev)\n      }\n      attributes(y) &lt;- list(levels = as.character(seq_along(lev)), class =\n\"factor\")\n      y\n    }\n    g &lt;- interaction(lapply(list(...), ifactor), drop = TRUE)\n    <http:\/\/is.na|is.na>(x) &lt;- <http:\/\/is.na|is.na>(g)\n    split(x, g) &lt;- lapply(split(x, g), FUN)\n  }\n  x\n}\n```\n```\n&gt; x &lt;- c(0, 0, 1, 1 + 1e-15, NA, NA, NaN, NaN)\n&gt; ave(11:18, x, FUN=seq_along)\n[1]  1  2  1  2 15 16  1  2\n&gt; ave_experimental(11:18, x, FUN=seq_along)\n[1]  1  2  1  1 NA NA NA NA\n&gt; ave_experimental(11:18, factor(x), FUN=seq_along)\n[1]  1  2  1  2 NA NA  1  2\n```\n|                                 | `1+1e-15` = `1`? | `NaN` = `NA`? |\n| :------------------------------ | :--------------: | :------------: |\n| `as.character`                  | Yes              | No             |\n| `unique`, `duplicated`, `match` | No               | No             |\n| `rank`, `sort`, `order`         | No               | Yes            |",
        "username": "r-bugs notifier",
        "icons": {
            "emoji": ":robot_face:"
        },
